    <title>Arctic contributor: Mark Nuttall</title>
    <description>Mark Nuttall is Professor and Henry Marshall Tory Chair of Anthropology at the University of Alberta. He also holds a visiting professorship at the Greenland Climate Research Centre/Greenland Institute of Natural Resources and Ilisimatusarfik, where he directs the Climate and Society Research Group. He is a coauthor (with Klaus Dodds) of “The Scramble for the Poles: The Geopolitics of the Arctic and Antarctic” (Polity, 2016).
</description>
